{
  "texts": [
    "For any possibility model M, s ∈ M, and φ ∈ L(Φ, I):1.",
    "M, s ⊩ φ iff the formula ST x (φ) is satisfied by s in M regarded as a first-order structure for L 1 (Φ, I);2.",
    "M ⊩ φ iff the sentence ST (φ) is true in M regarded as a first-order structure for L 1 (Φ, I).To have this kind of result at the level of frame validity, we move to the monadic second-order language L 2 (Φ, I) obtained from L 1 (I) by adding a predicate variable Q for each q ∈ Φ.",
    "We interpret L 2 (Φ, I) in possibility frames-or rather, foundations F ♯ = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I ⟩ of possibility frameswith ℘(S) as the domain for the monadic second-order quantifiers.",
    "We then relate the modal language L(Φ, I) to the second-order language L 2 (Φ, I) over full possibility frames using the following definition and proposition."
  ]
}